humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: According to the report, there are 3 positive lymph nodes out of 17 examined. Based on the AJCC staging system, this would correspond to an N1 stage. This is consistent with Rule 9, New Rule 10, and New Rule 11, as there are metastases in specific lymph nodes and all assessed lymph nodes are negative for metastatic carcinoma except for 3.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The N stage is determined by the number of lymph nodes involved. In this report, there are 3 positive axillary lymph nodes out of 17 examined. Therefore, the N stage is N1.
